Three bombs explode in Ukraine's Kirovograd hours before Yanukovych's arrival
Three bombs were detonated Friday in city of Kirovograd hours before country's President Viktor Yanukovych's arrival, local press reported. The bombs detonated in front of government offices in Kirovograd, it said. The Kirovohrad regional state prosecutor's office, regional court and a city police precinct were all targeted, according to media reports. Local press said one bomb exploded at night and two others in early morning. No casualties and injuries have been reported. According to preliminary investigation, explosive devices were selfmade with parts of shells used during the World War II. Yanukovych arrived in Kirovograd on a visit, 360 km southeast of Kiev, by helicopter.